The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a ceremony at the White House to honor law enforcement officers and first responders who displayed bravery and heroism in various situations. The President also addressed the recent school shooting in Parkland, Florida and emphasized the need to take concrete steps to improve school safety and protect children. He mentioned discussions with students, local leaders, and law enforcement to develop solutions and highlighted the importance of evidence-based approaches and better coordination between federal and state law enforcement. The President also announced that he signed a memorandum directing the Attorney General to propose regulations to ban devices that turn legal weapons into machine guns. He concluded by expressing gratitude to the honorees and reaffirming his commitment to finding solutions to prevent future tragedies.